# Bot Security Rules

## Secrets — NEVER hardcode

```python
# ❌ BAD
BOT_TOKEN = "123456:ABC-DEF..."

# ✅ GOOD
import os
from dotenv import load_dotenv
load_dotenv()
BOT_TOKEN = os.getenv("BOT_TOKEN")
if not BOT_TOKEN:
    raise ValueError("BOT_TOKEN not set in .env")
```

## .gitignore must always contain

```
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.db
audio_cache/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
```

## .env.example must be committed (no real values)

```env
BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
ADMIN_CHAT_ID=your_chat_id_here
MODE=polling
WEBHOOK_URL=
WEBHOOK_PORT=8443
```

## Input validation

- Never pass raw user text to shell commands or SQL without parameterized queries
- Use `?` placeholders in aiosqlite, never f-strings in SQL

## Webhook security

- Always verify `WEBHOOK_SECRET_TOKEN` header when in webhook mode
- Use HTTPS only for webhook URL
